		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Everybody WingChun tonite ! (Alternate Version)</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><table width='89' border='0' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='0'><tr><td background='/lotr/gfx/5star.gif'><img src='/lotr/gfx/trans.gif' width='1' height='25'></td></tr></table><font size=1>(4.46)</font> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=30330&PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=8523">Alexander "Eomer - RoR" Schwarz</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=8523&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> This Deck uses tons of direct damage and a fast cycling Dunland Shadow to get your Ringbearer safe to Site Nine.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> September 18, 2003</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Starting<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(175)">Frodo, Son of Drogo</a><br />
The One Ring, Isildurs Bane<br />
<br />
Free Peoples (32)<br />
