<br />
<br />
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> After i had submitted the first version, i had to think long and hard, to make the deck better.<br />
<br />
The problems the deck faced were three-fold :<br />
<br />
First off, it was very vulnerable to Sarumans Power, with all those conditions, which evidently in conjunction with Bilbo doubled as my condition removal. So, if i ran into Uruks, i was screwed big time, especially, if i didnt have PATHS OR i had to burn instead of saving them for the win at site nine.<br />
<br />
Second problem was, that although it was was ok vs. Non-palantir Moria, it had trouble at the very least at site nine, if the opponent removed your hand, or played Snows, since there was no Gandalf, hence no Dreary - the last fact made it impossible to run six companions, because even if you face Uruks and there is no Enquea, there might be Greed.<br />
<br />
Third, and last the companions generally dont win much skirmishes, plus there was no healing power, which made everything vulnerable to minion archery; you even had to exert for Gondor Bowmen, which is an additional wound. Plus, Twilight Nazgul wounding the Ringbearer might lead to too many burdens early on, and punishment through Nazgul Sword, Toldea and Enquea.<br />
<br />
So, what to do ?<br />
<br />
I decided to focus on direct damage, and included defend it and hope to deal with uruks, should my bowmen be powered away, or i have no Aragorns Bow at hand. Naturally, that meant, vs. the Palantir i HAD to include Erland, because cycling in this Deck becomes quite essential.<br />
<br />
However, that meant i had to drop Legolas, but i was able to get Gandalf and Lindenroot, which meant i hardly die to Moria AND help with cycling.<br />
<br />
Merry, Faramir & Gandalf all have the Frodo signet, so i can be sure that Twilight Nazgul wont become too dangerous for the Ringbearer.<br />
<br />
-----<br />
<br />
Strategy : <br />
<br />
Bid 6 to 7 to start the game.<br />
<br />
Naturally, you will bid 6 to six most of the time,<br />
and only bid 7 when you are sure that you will face Moria. Some Moria builds even bid high to let you start, which you definitely want to.<br />
<br />
Get Gorn from the Riddermark, and play Map and Bowman, if you have, in order to cycle.<br />
<br />
Since Nazgul can be a pain, you should look for some direct damage in your opening hand, or things might get rough.<br />
<br />
Generally, if possible, you should try to make site three in one move, since that means you will be able to control up to two sites at most, if your opponent follows your example.<br />
<br />
With your fellowship you should stay in the lead, as reaching site nine alive, and surviving there, is the primary goal for you to win the game.<br />
<br />
Your shadow strategy is actually quite easy :<br />
<br />
You play the minions in hand, and everything you cannot play, dump into the discard pile.<br />
<br />
Lindenroot can be a boon to achieve that.<br />
<br />
If your opponent ever doubles on you, slap down Constantly threatening, and get the minions out of the discard pile, to control sites.<br />
<br />
Note, that you generally only ever need to control one site, if you go for the fellowship win, that one site activates Over the Isen and the Hill Chief, whom you continuosly play from your discard pile, if the twilight is sufficient to topdeck the cards you need for your fellowship win.<br />
<br />
Matchups :<br />
<br />
I dont have playtested this deck at all, and it may drastically change, so i can only type this from my experience at playing the game.<br />
<br />
Uruks (Tracker, Battleground) :<br />
<br />
Lindenroot, and Defend It and Hope greatly help here - dont stack on Gondor Bowmen, play them as soon as they hit the table, so your opponent does not get Card advantage from using Sarumans Power.<br />
<br />
Dreary gets to discard Wearies and the Ambitions, to ensure that you dont take too many wounds, or get overwhelmed on the spot. The Deck does not contain any battlegrounds, so it might be not a bad call to let your opponent get ahead of you one site, and therefore ensure that his Vanguards, Advanced Uruk Patrols do not get to use their gametext. Aragorn is a 12 vs. the green Uglies, Lindenroot is a 10 and Boromir or Gandalf can be power 10 or 11 if pumped by Merry.<br />
<br />
If they have the sword, you can use Lindenroot to kill one guy, only do that if you want to double or prevent more wounds or dead guys on your side.<br />
<br />
Nazgul :<br />
<br />
The key vs. Nazgul here is the combination of using Gondor Bowmen (huge !!), Archery and direct damage. Dont make foolish double moves, and if you do move double, ensure that potentially lethal minions, like the Twilight Witchking with Fell Beast do not leave the table to soon, so that he  can play another.<br />
<br />
There are no Plains in this deck, either but Black Steed is generally not so much used anymore.<br />
<br />
Definitely stay at two burdens, since three activates the Sword. If you are forced to exert people for Toldea, Winged Sentry, by all means use Boromir, who can get healed next turn.<br />
<br />
If they go condition heavy, keep your Grown Suddenly Tall, after they have amassed quite a number of Breaths and Tips and use Grown Suddenly Tall after that. Doubling after flooding the pool is generally not a good idea, unless you have tons of direct damage in your hand.<br />
<br />
Make sure you wasted all your gondor bowmen before playing GST, though.<br />
<br />
Moria :<br />
<br />
Moria is what people call an &quot;advantaged matchup&quot;.<br />
<br />
The Deck has Gandalf, who definitely wrecks Moria, plus tons of direct damage, so youre not screwed if the get the Archery combo, unless you dont find your erland to prevent the Palantirs gametext. Try to find your Thrors Map before site 7, so you dont have to deal with the Cavern Entrance. Generally while doubling you must use good judgement, it is all about what conditions they have, what events in your hand, do you have the pan, and whatnot. Never double from three to five, or from two to four, if Frodo does not have the pan ! Vs the Archery Combo, you can use Defend it and Hope to kill the weak link, and fire away. If they play Black Traitior with Staff at site five, its a sure sign, that they use the Orthanc Balcony as their site nine, and PROBABLY Sarumans Snows, so try to keep your Dreary and not play him before the fellowship phase at Valley of Saruman. Of course, heal your Frodo with pan by exerting the other guys, and the Guard Commander always goes on Faramir, who kills it with Merry exerting to pump him.<br />
<br />
Be wary of Balrog and Troll.<br />
<br />
Dunland :<br />
<br />
Again, here it is all about the direct damage you get, and the Hides they have from the beginning.<br />
<br />
Since you start the game, you have the best possibility of doubling to three, if your hand is good - a thing you normally would never do against Dunland, as this spells certain doom for one of your companions.<br />
<br />
Since you use Site Control, too you should be in a position to steal the site right under your opponents nose, therefore incapicating his shadow side. You almost exclusively have to rely on your direct damage, as losing skirmishes can have a profound and later on game-ending effect.<br />
<br />
Remember, both Over the Isen and Constantly Threatening only ever need one site to be controlled in order to work.<br />
<br />
Try to hit their Site Controllers, never double when Constantly Threatening is out & you have a chance of surviving and winning this.<br />
<br />
Just like shadow archery, you should try for the shadow win, generally.<br />
<br />
Minion Archery :<br />
<br />
Now, i dont need to tell you that Minion ARchery currently celebrates a huge comeback in the tournament scene - Moria Archery is probably again an advantaged matchup, as you have Gandalf, and the healing Boromir.<br />
<br />
Make sure that you hit as much They ARe Comings and swarms as possible with GST, as TAC allows him to play one or two Moria Archer Troops each turn, and if you allow him to stack the archers, who will generally always win their skirmishes, its game.<br />
<br />
Uruk Archery is a bit different, as those minions pack quite some more punch.<br />
<br />
Just like Moria Archery, you will single move in this matchup, because most of the decks pack the biggies which can seriously hurt you.<br />
<br />
Uruk Archery may pack tons of Sarumans Power, that means your Gondor Bowmen are worthless.<br />
<br />
You can use Defend It And Hope sparingly to kill Lurtz as he can wreck havoc among your companions.<br />
<br />
Use Dreary to kill the loaded, and only the loaded Weapons of Isengard.<br />
<br />
If they play Tower of Orthanc you should make sure that no companion is exhausted.<br />
<br />
Beware of Caradhras has not forgiven us, which will discard a key companion, and for rogue cards like Saruman, Servant of the Eye.<br />
<br />
Shadow side :<br />
<br />
I will only write a short paragraph here, as this strategy section is long enough, already.<br />
<br />
Generally, you will take their capability of winning skirmishes with the club, and get more sites after the first, by Over the Isen.<br />
<br />
Vs. Archery, if they have Allies, use the Warrior with a Club to discard Aragorns Bow.<br />
<br />
Use any opportunity to take sites, since the Hillman Horde will cancel the whole Archery phase, after taking two, and nearly no Deck has site liberation cards with them.<br />
<br />
Vs. Dauntless Hunter, you kill Merry and Pippin, and its all over - this deck cannot double against the shadow, and if it does, you WILL most of the time get your first side.<br />
<br />
Vs. Ents, they cannot double with Constantly Threatening out, because each time you get Sarumand and two minions and take the next site.<br />
<br />
You kill their weaker companions, and if they double after that, you will overwhelm Frodo with a swarm.<br />
<br />
Generally never waste your Hides, you need them for Site nine, if worse comes to worse, rather let your minions die against too much archery !<br />
<br />
Dont worry, if you have not gotten a single site and still have to go for the shadow kill, if your opponent does not have enough companions, and you can get out Hillman Horde and two Tribes, you can still win the game !<br />
<br />
Have Fun !<br />
<br />
Cheers,<br />
<br />
Eomer </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=30330&PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=30330&PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
